The paper deals with the problem of constructing linear maps that satisfy a restricted isometry property (RIP) on an arbitrary signal model, which is a common topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses techniques for constructing these linear maps, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper applies its results to several examples, which involves signal processing (cs.SP).
